{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> συμβουλ-εύω</b>, <br /> <b>advise, counsel</b>, with <i>dative</i> <i>person</i> et <i>infinitive</i>, <b>advise</b> one to do a thing, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.53, 59, 2.107, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.65, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οὐ συμβουλεύων Ερξῃ στρατεύεσθαι <b>advising</b> him not.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.46: rarely with _accusative_ et \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>infinitive</i>, συμβουλεύω.. συμβῆναι ὑμᾶς I <b>advise</b> that you should.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 337e, compare 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 16.501. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> without <i>infinitive</i>, σ. τινί τι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.71, etc.; ὅτι ἂν δύνωνται ἀγαθὸν Ἀθηναίοις “IG” 12.106.19; τοῖς ὀλίγον διαπνεομένοις ἀσιτίαν 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 15.508; τινὶ περί τινος 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 319d, etc.; εὖ σ. τινί 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 38 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; σ. τι <b>recommend</b> a measure, τὰ ἄριστα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.237; χρηστόν τι 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 793; πορείαν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 5.6.12, etc.: but with _accusative_ _cognate_, σ. συμβουλάς\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>give</b> advice, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 520d:\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] —<i>passive</i>, συμβουλεύεταί τι <b>advice is given</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Ep.” 330d; τὰ παρὰ τῶν θεῶν συμβουλευόμενα 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 1.6.2; τὰ συμβουλευθέντα 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 3.13; τὰ -βεβουλευμένα \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>res de consilii sententia actae,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Inscriptiones Graecae 7.413.58 (Oropus, 1st c.BC, Senatus consultum) \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]; of persons, <b>to be advised</b>, ὑπό τινος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “POxy.” 118.3 (3rd c.AD). \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> followed by a <i>relative</i>, σ. περί τινος ὡς.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “de Vectigalibus” 4.30; σύμ μοι βούλευσον, ποτέρην ἄγω 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Epigrammata” 1.5. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> <i>absolutely</i>, <b>advise, give advice</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 1370, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὁ συμβουλεύων or -εύσας <b>adviser</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1354b31, Legal cited in 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 1.96 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὰ συμβουλεύοντα τῶν ποιημάτων <b>didactic</b> poems, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 2.42. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>middle</i>, <b>consult with</b> a person, i.e. <b>ask</b> his <b>advice</b>, τινι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.107, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Epistulae” 331a, “Thg.” 122a, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τι in a matter, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 8.68 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; σ. τι μετά τινος <b>debate</b> a matter with another, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 475 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>absolutely</i>, <b>consult, deliberate</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 2.1.7, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] —<i>active</i> and <i>middle</i> opposed, συμβουλευομένου ἂν συμβουλεύσειε τὰ ἄριστα <b>if one asked his advice</b> he <b>would give</b> him the best, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.237; [τοῖς Ἕλλησι] συμβουλευομένοις συνεβούλευσε τάδε 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 2.1.17. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> = <i>active</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"Scholia 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Scutum Herculis” 338, _falsa lectio_ in 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 6.5.34. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <b>agree, make a contract</b>, θύρας λιθίνης ἧς συνεβουλεύσατο κόψαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PMich.Zen.” 37.3 (3rd c.BC). \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G4823","accentedUnicode":"συμβουλεύω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G1011","matchingForm":"βουλεύω","stepTransliteration":"bouleuō","gloss":"to plan","_zh_tw_Gloss":"商議","_es_Gloss":"planear ","_zh_Gloss":"商议"},{"strongNumber":"G4862","matchingForm":"σύν","stepTransliteration":"sun","gloss":"with","_zh_tw_Gloss":"同, 一同, 和","_es_Gloss":"con","_zh_Gloss":"同, 一同, 和"}],"shortDef":"to advise, counsel; (<i>middle</i>) to plot, conspire, consult","mediumDef":"to advise, counsel; (<i>middle</i>) to plot, conspire, consult <br /><b>to counsel, advise, exhort,</b> <ref='Jhn.18.14'>Jn. 18:14</ref>; <ref='Rev.3.18'>Rev. 3:18;</ref> <i>middle</i> <b>to consult together, plot, conspire</b> <ref='Mat.26.4'>Mt. 26:4</ref>; <ref='Act.9.23'>Acts 9:23</ref>*","stepGloss":"to consult","stepTransliteration":"sumbouleuō","count":4,"_es_Definition":"aconsejar, asesorar ; (voz media) consultar, conspirar","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 給予忠告<br>2) 與別人一起計劃, 商量, 諮詢<br>3) 思索, 考量","_zh_Definition":"1) 给予忠告<br>2) 与别人一起计划, 商量, 咨询<br>3) 思索, 考量","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"khuyên. σύν (G4862) + βουλεύω (G1011)","_zh_tw_Gloss":"商議","_es_Gloss":"consultar","_zh_Gloss":"商议"}]}